Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on coordination of robot swarms and proposes a novel algorithm for navigation and connectivity maintenance.
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the paper deals with a large decentralized team of robots and proposes a method for maintaining communication between them.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with controlling a group of robots in complex environments.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with maintaining connectivity between robots.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel algorithm for navigation and connectivity maintenance.
